Description: 
    Implements a two-stage Bayesian hierarchical modeling framework for
    applying shrinkage to subgroup-specific effects. The package separates
    model fitting (Stage 1) from hierarchical shrinkage (Stage 2), enabling
    modular sensitivity analyses without refitting expensive MCMC chains.
    Supports flexible prior specifications through the distributional package,
    mixture approximations via mclust, and efficient Stan-based inference.
